			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Bard&message.id=4071#M4071">9</a> of 30
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 708 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>UGGGG ok here's my beef with the Bard Epic 1.5:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>1) Guild Epic Policy:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Our guild has a pretty decent Epic policy that we use to help folks achieve their 1.5s.&nbsp; We basically go 1st ready, 1st raided.&nbsp; We've completed a number of Epic 1.5s, and a Bard is currently at the top of the list.&nbsp; We've spent soooo much time on&nbsp;this single Bard 1.5 quest that other classes are getting hosed when it comes to doing their raids.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>2) Member Reluctance to help with Epics:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Because of the stupid amount of time we've spent on this Bard epic,&nbsp;alot of folks are very put off with the idea of using guild resources to help with Epic 1.5's to begin with, and some are now even refusing to join&nbsp;Epic Raids even though DKP is earned.&nbsp; Now do we tell this bard "hey sorry, your quest sucks so much we're not gonna finish it, even though you were ready 1st, we're moving on to others" or do we say "sorry guild, you're hosed and no one gets their epic until we finish this bard quest because he was ready first".&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>(I'm not here to debate our guild epic policy, so please don't offer...its worked 100% up until the Bard)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>3) Too Many Raids Required for a Single Epic:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>First off, for the target audience that 1.5's are aimed at, this is the only Epic 1.5 that Requires <FONT size=4>FIVE </FONT>raids.&nbsp; Monks come in 2nd with 4 raids....every other class has basically 3 raids or less.&nbsp; That right there should send up a screaming red flag that says "Hey, sumpthin ain't right here...what gives?"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>4) Difficulty of the Final DN Event is Rediculous:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>The NK, JPF,&nbsp;and SB dragons were not too bad, but hey they are dragons, so it was fun.&nbsp; We did the 1st DN encounter with very little problems.&nbsp; Wasn't so bad, other than all the newer players who've never regularly raided ToV&nbsp;getting raped&nbsp;in SG /sigh.&nbsp; So we go back for round 2 in DN.....you gotta be kidding me!&nbsp; We just beat the Rathe Counsil last week to become a Time Guild....and we can't even beat a Bard 1.5 quest aimed at pre-EP guilds?&nbsp; Wha-wha-WHAT?&nbsp; You'd think that after all 4 dragons and the 1st DN raid, that SOE would be forgiving enough to have a not-so-insane last fight.&nbsp; But most importantly - this event is NOT FUN.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We gave up after 3 tries, went out to WW, and killed the final target for one of our SKs 1.5.&nbsp; The difficulty between the Bard and SK encounters is night and day.&nbsp; So much for balance.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>5) Final DN Event is BUGGED (iceing on the cake)</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Thats right.&nbsp; We went back yesterday to try again.&nbsp; This time we are prepared.&nbsp; Strats hammered out,&nbsp;and&nbsp;had roughly 60 people, with plenty of offtanks and chanters&nbsp;(we are Time flagged, but not Time geared, though much loot has been gotten from MPG trials etc etc, so we ain't exactly slouches).&nbsp; One&nbsp;of the minions was still up from a previous attempt.&nbsp; I saw it, but none of the leaders or the Bard saw it.&nbsp; I figured it was maybe part of the event....sorta like a PH to tell if the event was triggerable or whatever.....boy was I ever wrong.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So bard zones in and triggers event, I set assign the offtanks....but.....we botched it due to early agro.&nbsp; Now, granted a mistake was made, but with the number and calibre of the people there, this should have been easily overcome and recovered from.&nbsp; Newp.&nbsp; After the wipe, we get reports of people getting hit for 30,000 -&nbsp;40,000 - 50,000 - 60,000.&nbsp; Now I'm thinking the same thing as you....yeah maybe an extra 0 was added.&nbsp; No sir...let me spell it out.....single melee hits for SIXTY THOUSAND points of damage.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So we do the CR and rezzes, we come to the conclusion that someone must have been running in and out of teather range resetting the mobs, and thats why we were getting those outrageous melee hits from the minions.&nbsp; We set up again, let the event despawn, and start all over.&nbsp;&nbsp;All is going well....cool looks like we'll finally beat this stupid thing.&nbsp; Then....a mezz is broken.&nbsp; No biggy, it happens.&nbsp; But guess what....that broken mezz happened to be the bugged minion that never despawned.&nbsp; One by one, people start dropping....more reports of 50,000-60,000 single melee hits.&nbsp; BAM minion hits YOU for 54,378 points of damage!&nbsp; Loading please wait.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So, I ask the bard....is that minion supposed to stay there when everything else despawns?&nbsp; Bard replies...CRAP its BUGGED again <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-sad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV><p>Message Edited by Hulkling on <span class=date_text>05-24-2005</span> <span class=time_text>04:21 PM</span>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
