		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Alastriona wrote:<BR>
<DIV>for the difficulty of the NK and JP dragons, they should drop chests..why don't they?</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I believe one of the reasons they don't is because they aren't triggerable by bards--anyone can go up and whack the animals to spawn and kill the dragon.&nbsp; If they simply had them drop chests without redoing the way they were spawned people could just farm them and we'd have the bottleneck of having constantly farmed mobs that would never be up.&nbsp; All other epic 1.5-2.0 chest encounters drop from one-time triggered events, unless I am mistaken.&nbsp; So it's a tradeoff of whether we want to have mobs which require no previous epic work to kill (at the expense of having absolutely no loot table besides the pieces) or have them triggered by the bard and drop a chest.&nbsp; I'm not sure which would be better <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>And as to the Dragon Necropolis second fight, I had a ton of problems with multiple spawns of zombies/skeletons and other fun stuff.&nbsp; When I petitioned and spoke with one of the lead FV GM's, I was told they were unable to despawn the encounter and to make sure I was "doing the quest step correctly".&nbsp; The way I deal with this bug is to wait the full despawn time (14 minutes or so) and keep logging out and back in until all the duplicates eventually despawn.&nbsp; To save time, show up in DN around an hour before a scheduled epic raid and go through this process until you have ensured the encounter has fully despawned for you, then just hang out there or outside DN until you're ready for the encounter.</P><p>Message Edited by Booperbustle on <span class=date_text>05-26-2005</span> <span class=time_text>09:14 AM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
