			<br><blockquote><hr>Booperbustle wrote:<br><DIV></DIV><BR><BLOCKQUOTE><HR>Alastriona wrote:<BR><DIV>for the difficulty of the NK and JP dragons, they should drop chests..why don't they?</DIV><BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><DIV></DIV><P>I believe one of the reasons they don't is because they aren't triggerable by bards--anyone can go up and whack the animals to spawn and kill the dragon.  If they simply had them drop chests without redoing the way they were spawned people could just farm them and we'd have the bottleneck of having constantly farmed mobs that would never be up.  All other epic 1.5-2.0 chest encounters drop from one-time triggered events, unless I am mistaken.  So it's a tradeoff of whether we want to have mobs which require no previous epic work to kill (at the expense of having absolutely no loot table besides the pieces) or have them triggered by the bard and drop a chest.  I'm not sure which would be better <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P><hr></blockquote><br><br><br>Cipheron, the Swarmcaller, the girplans in rcod, the girplan in WoS/Mpg and many many mores mobs  arnt triggered and they can drop chest. The chest actually pop When someone who is flagged loot the piece. The same mechanic could be added to when a "flagged" bard loot the crystal. <br><br>However, consider this. You can kill the dragons whenever and they will drop the crystal, bard or not. Also, this mean there is absolutly no flag you need to get before you can loot the piece. On top of that, the respawn is pretty fast. So.. any one can create a lvl 1 bard and just kill the dragon and have the newbie bard loot the peice and that would pop a chest ?<br><br>The way the dragons are implemented in the quest doesnt allow them to drop chest. Is it a flaw in the quest? i think so. Would it require a lot of work to fix this? yes. Does it really worth the time/$ of devs to change that ? First off, i don't think so. Secondly, I would prefer they work on something else.
