<DIV>2 DN events</DIV>
<DIV>4 dragons</DIV>
<DIV>1 kithicor event</DIV>
<DIV>1 torment battle </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For 2.0:</DIV>
<DIV>Loot the orb from angish</DIV>
<DIV>Loot 3 chaos pieces</DIV>
<DIV>Final battle</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The DN events have nothing to do with the 1.5 as far as I can see.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For 1.5: </DIV>
<DIV>4 dragons</DIV>
<DIV>1 kithicor event</DIV>
<DIV>1 torment battle</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For 2.0:</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>2 DN events</DIV>
<DIV>Loot the orb from angish</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Loot 3 chaos pieces</DIV>
<DIV>Final battle</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1.5 would still have six events, and our 2.0 would be more in line with others. (From what I can see Bard 2.0 is pretty easy after getting 1.5.... makes up for the 8 1.5 events for Anguish guilds... but not for pre-Anguish guilds).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have my 1.5 and now that Cloud mentions it yes, the AE dispell is too much.&nbsp; With buffs perhaps non uberguilds could handle those dragons but when they do not have uber gear and you spam them with dispell it's way too harsh.&nbsp; For our guild they are probably single groupable now, but I feel bad that the spam dispell makes them extremely difficult for people without such gear.&nbsp; I've never seen the events personally before being in a GoD guild so really I'm not in a position to personally say how out of balance the dispell is, but I could imagine with lesser gear mercilessly stripping off all the buffs leaves very little protection from the AEs.</DIV></DIV></DIV><p>Message Edited by Zunnoab-Stromm on <span class=date_text>06-06-2005</span> <span class=time_text>08:57 AM</span>	
