			I've lead a few DN1/2 fights, for 2 I've seen this happen. I leashed em and faded(be extra sure with agro clear). They despawned after the set time for event. Try this as a shot, otherwise learn to actually scout your epics on epic days. Takes 5min to get to DN, then 20 for event to despawn and see if any are still up. Do this a few hours before raid and you'll probably get a GM to despawn them by raid time. As far as DN2's difficulty, I lead a raid(32 people iirc) of EP people(not time flagged yet), with a few 1.5s in there, on this. They did one of the cleanest runs I've ever seen and fast(gj In Via Damnum). This raid is not hard, it's about strat and then massive dps on the construct. As for the dragons I have to agree though, tone them down to a 1-2 group fight for EP level people. AEs are harsh and the AE ramp on the one or so doesnt help at all considering the hitbox range. With them being in wide open areas you cant range fight any besides the mountain one, and thats with **HALFLING** careful placement, so range fight and healing the tank is out for most of them.<br><br>While more and more guilds are Time+ now, timeplane is still not "casual" or EP like they said, I just dont see how time level is "working as intended."<br><br>I also agree on the multitude of raids. My guild is just about to enter Uqua, and we dread the bard 1.5. Not because its hard or terribly long timewise, with right spawns could easily do in 1 saturday/sunday. But when we get an app that doesnt have the first thing in our minds is "**HALFLING**, now we have to do 8 **HALFLING** raids that take away from the guild getting loot thats usable besides the actual epic." If nothing else, scale up the chest loot, and add more than um...2(?).. chests in our quest.	
